A MANHUNT is underway today after a schoolgirl was chased by a beer-bellied creep.The 14-year-old was walking home in Kilmarnock when a silver car pulled up in London Road, opposite Gray's Fuel.Police said a man - who is described as having a beer belly and shaved head - got out of the vehicle and started chasing her.It happened at around 10p mon Thursday and police have warned the public to be aware of the suspect, who is thought to be in his 40s.Officers urged anyone else who may have been targeted and chased by him to come forward.The girl kept running and managed to get away.She hasn't seen the man or the car since.The suspect is described as between 40 and 50-years-old, around 5ft 9in tall, of stocky build with a beer belly, and shaved head.At the time of the incident, he was wearing a dark, short sleeved top and black jogging bottoms.A small green car, which was being driven by a woman, was also seen in the area at the time.The female driver is understood to have shouted from the car to the 14-year-old to &quot;keep running, he's coming&quot;.A Police Scotland spokesman said: &quot;Police at Kilmarnock would like to speak to anyone who has any information regarding this incident or anyone else who was approached by this man.&quot;Information should be passed to Police Scotland via telephone number 101.&quot;